  • Field Details

    • coord

      @VoDml(id="meas:Position.coord", role=attribute, type="coords:Point", typeRole=dataType) protected Point coord
      The measured Position value. The Point coordinate supports 1,2, and 3-dimensional cases. Details of the coordinate system (space and frame), are associated with the Point. : Attribute coord : multiplicity 1

    • Position

      public Position(Point coord, String ucd, Error error)
      full parameter constructor.
      Parameters:
      coord - The measured Position value. The Point coordinate supports 1,2, and 3-dimensional cases. Details of the coordinate system (space and frame), are associated with the Point.
      ucd - The Unified Content Descriptor (UCD) defines a controlled vocabulary for describing astronomical quantities. Other than in the specialized types, we only constrain ucd value to being valid according to the vocabulary syntax. However, the intent is to use only enough of the vocabulary to convey the nature of the measured value, and avoid usage of terms which may overlap with modeled concepts associated with the value. For example, borrowing from examples in the UCD document: for a magnitude measured in the J band, the ucd 'phot.mag' is preferred over 'phot.mag;em.IR.J' which conveys information about an associated filter, or 'phot.mag;em.IR.J;meta.modelled' which includes ancillary qualifiers.
      error - Measurement error.
